        flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "message", existingErrorMessage + errorMessage)
    }

    if (transformCallback.errorOccurred || transformCallback.validationFailed) {
        session.transfer(flowFile, REL_FAILURE)
    } else {
        session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
    }

        return errorMap.getOrDefault(errorCode, "Unknown error")
    }

// Retrieve the FlowFile from the session
def flowFile = session.get()
if (flowFile != null) {
    // Create the TransformCallback instance and pass the log
    def transformCallback = new TransformCallback(log)

    // Write the FlowFile using the callback
    flowFile = session.write(flowFile, transformCallback)
	def message = flowFile.getAttribute('message')
    if (message) {
        // Escape the message
        def escapedMessage = transformCallback.escapeJsonString(message)
        // Add the escaped message back to a new attribute
        flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "message", escapedMessage)
    }
    // Add the extracted ids as a single attribute (failed_ids)
	if (transformCallback.ids) {
        // Create a JSON string with the ids as an array
        def failedIdsJson = JsonOutput.toJson([ids: transformCallback.ids])
        flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "additional_metadata", failedIdsJson)
    }
	def errorCode = flowFile.getAttribute('error.sql.state')

    if (errorCode) {
        // Get the error message for the code
        def existingErrorMessage = flowFile.getAttribute('message') ?: ""
        def errorMessage = transformCallback.getErrorMessageForCode(errorCode)
        // Set the error message as a new attribute
        flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "message", existingErrorMessage + errorMessage)
    }

    // Transfer to the appropriate relationship
    if (transformCallback.errorOccurred || transformCallback.validationFailed) {
        session.transfer(flowFile, REL_FAILURE)
    } else {
        session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
    }
}

WITH person_check AS (
    SELECT person_key
    FROM ${db_name}.person_cross_reference pcr
    INNER JOIN ${db_name}.client_person cp ON (pcr.client_person_key = cp.client_person_key)
    WHERE pcr.application_person_id = '${participant_id}'
    LIMIT 1
)
INSERT INTO ${db_name}.project_candidate (
    cohort_project_key,
    candidate_key,
    date_created,
    status_date,
    is_completed_flag,
    status,
    is_non_billable
)
SELECT
    (SELECT DISTINCT cohort_project_key FROM ${db_name}.cohort_project WHERE source_project_id = '${projectId}' LIMIT 1),
    (SELECT person_key FROM person_check),
    '${created_date}',
    CAST(NULLIF('${participantDeadline}', 'null') AS DATE),
    CASE WHEN '${status}' = 'All Surveys Complete' THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END,
    '${status}',
    CAST(NULLIF('${is_non_billable}', 'null') AS BOOLEAN)
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM person_check WHERE person_key IS NOT NULL
)
ON CONFLICT (cohort_project_key, candidate_key)
DO UPDATE SET
    date_created = EXCLUDED.date_created,
    status_date = EXCLUDED.status_date,
    is_completed_flag = EXCLUDED.is_completed_flag,
    status = EXCLUDED.status,
    is_non_billable = EXCLUDED.is_non_billable
RETURNING project_candidate_key;

WITH keys AS (
select ar.role_key as role_key, am.model_key as model_key,c.client_key as client_key from ${db_name}.a360_role ar,
${db_name}.a360_model am 
, ${db_name}.client c
where ar.client_key = am.client_key and ar.role_key=am.role_key and ar.source_role_id=${kF360RoleId}
and c.is_active =true and c.is_deleted =false and c.sap_client_id = '${sapClientId}'
)
INSERT INTO ${db_name}.a360_participant_assessment (
    project_candidate_key, 
    source_assessment_id, 
    instrument,
    status,
	role_key,
	model_key
)
SELECT 
    '${project_candidate_pkey}',
    '${assessment_source_id}',
    NULLIF('${assessment_type}', 'null'),
    NULLIF('${assessment_status}', 'null'),
	(select role_key from keys),
	(select model_key from keys)

ON CONFLICT (project_candidate_key, source_assessment_id)  
DO UPDATE SET
    instrument = EXCLUDED.instrument,
    status = EXCLUDED.status,
	role_key =  EXCLUDED.role_key,
	model_key = EXCLUDED.model_key;

WITH rater_type AS (
    SELECT rater_type_key 
    FROM ${db_schema}.a360_rater_type 
    WHERE rater_id = '${id}' 
    LIMIT 1
)
INSERT INTO ${db_schema}.a360_participant_assessment_status (
    participant_assessment_key, 
    rater_type_key, 
    total_submitted, 
    total_distributed, 
    total_submitted_valid
)
VALUES (
    '${sql.generated.key}', 
    (SELECT rater_type_key FROM rater_type), 
    ${surveysCompleted}, 
    ${surveysDistributed}, 
    ${surveysWithValidData}
)
ON CONFLICT (participant_assessment_key, rater_type_key)
DO UPDATE SET
    total_submitted = EXCLUDED.total_submitted,
    total_distributed = EXCLUDED.total_distributed,
    total_submitted_valid = EXCLUDED.total_submitted_valid
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM rater_type
    WHERE rater_type_key IS NOT NULL
)
RETURNING participant_assessment_status_key;
